#   BRO-004: colored `diff:` render — added-side flush (LANDED) + first-hunk incoherence (LANDED) + context-line dup (REOPENED Part 3)

Part 1 (LANDED `fc906b77`): `be --color diff:` dropped the *added (`+`) side* of a
change — fixed by a trailing-row flush in bro's two-pass renderer. Part 2 (LANDED
`2e271665`): colour first-hunk incoherence (mid-word splits, interleaving, em-dash
line duplicated) — fixed in the block-end scan. *Part 3 (REOPENED 2026-06-16):* a
single-line INSERT duplicates the adjacent CONTEXT line — colour renders it as both
removed and inserted; `--plain` is correct. Evidence: [iteration-dup] (Part 3),
[diff-incoherence] (Part 2). Method: [Issues].

