##  Outcome
 -  Part 1 LANDED `fc906b77`. *Part 2 LANDED `2e271665`*: root cause
    `bro/BRO.c:624-630` (`bro_walk_hunk` block-end scan broke at an eq-context segment
    even when the boundary `\n` into it was on the RM side, so the shared eq tail line
    rendered TWICE / interleaved). Fix: break at an eq segment only when the boundary
    `\n` is EQ-side (`&& (j==i || info[j-1].bnd_side==TOK_SIDE_EQ)`). New
    `test/diff/15-color-emdash-coherent` (RED→GREEN) + `test/diff/INDEX.md` entry;
    300/300 before and after. Confirmed independent of [ABC-003].
 -  *Part 3 LANDED `0dd4e0ba`* (FF child of `8d66369c`; msg `BRO-004: colour insert no
    longer dups context line`): colour duplicated the
    context line adjacent to a single-line insert. Producer was CORRECT (TLV toks mark
    the line EQ, the insert block all-IN incl. its `\n`); the bug was bro's render. Root
    cause: the *Part-2 block-end gate was TOO BROAD* — it treated ANY non-EQ boundary
    `\n` as a row continuation, so a pure insert's `IN`-side `\n` pulled the following EQ
    line into the change block (emitted on both rm + in sides). Fix (`bro/BRO.c` only):
    `bro_line_continues()` — a non-EQ boundary `\n` continues a row only when its side is
    HIDDEN from the pass rendering the prior line's content (`IN` `\n` continues an RM
    line, `RM` `\n` continues an IN line); a self-terminating pure insert/delete does NOT
    continue, so the next EQ line correctly breaks the block. New
    `test/diff/16-color-insert-context` (RED→GREEN); preserves Parts 1/2 (diff-14/15);
    *303/303*.

